AGI - An attack on firearms > was taken tonight at the Iraqi consulate of Istanbu>l. According to the statements made by the spokesman of the Foreign Ministry of Ankara 2 people on a motorcycle exploded 9 gunshots against the Iraqi diplomatic representation building, in the Sisli > district, on the European bank of the metropolis on the Bosphorus. No one was injured.&nbsp;
The tension in the Turkish metropolis is very high.&nbsp; Turkish opposition leader Ozgur Ozel> said that more than 300,000 people > participated in mass protests throughout Istanbul > following the arrest of the mayor of the city, Ekrem Imamoglu>. "We are 300,000 people," said the leader of the CHP> to the vast crowd in front of the municipality, stating that the protesters had gathered in several places in Turkey's largest city because of the closures of roads and bridges that prevented people from staying in the same place.
<h2> Meetings between protesters and police
There have been clashes in Istanbul > and Smirne> between protesters and police during demonstrations undetected by the opposition in support of the mayor of Istanbul, arrested Wednesday. In Istanbul, the police used rubber bullets > while in Smirne, the third largest city in the country, the police used hydrants >, according to local television footage.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h2> Arrests and prohibitions
Interior Minister Ali Yerlikaya> announced that 97 people were arrested throughout Turkey this evening, following the clashes between police and protesters that took place during the protest processions for the arrest of the mayor of Istanbul, Ekrem Imamoglu. Despite the prohibitions decided by the prefectures, the protesters crowded the squares of the capital Ankara>, of the third center of the country Smirne>, but above all Istanbul, where several tens of thousands of people crowded the square in front of the commune in the district of Sarachane>. After a rally attended by several politicians near Imamoglu, including the party secretary Ozgur Ozel, some protesters marched trying to reach Taksim > square, but they clashed with the police who with tear gas and charges stopped the procession. Scontri also took place in Smyrna and Ankara, where the police used hydrants and tear gas to disperse the crowd.
